==Scots Gaelic==
===Prepositional pronoun===
#[[at]] [[us]]

contraction of 'aig sinn' which literally means 'at us'.  It can be used to indicate possession

e.g. [[tha]] [[taigh]] againn - [[we]] [[have]] a [[house]] (literally 'a house is at us').

'againn' is not usually used to denote permanent ownership - the word 'leinn' is used when ownership is asserted.  tha taigh leinn - we [[own]] a [[house]].